{"name": "edgegap-settings", "metadata": {"name": "edgegap-settings", "version": "1.8.3", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pydantic-settings", "pydantic", "python-dotenv", "edgegap-logging", "edgegap-consul", "python-logstash-async", "elastic-apm"], "summary": "The Edgegap Settings library includes various tools and helpers for interacting with Explicit Settings Models. It is designed for use within the Edgegap organization.", "upload_time": 1732137339}, "documentation": ["# Edgegap Settings Library\n\nThis is the README for the Edgegap Settings Helper, which is part of the Edgegap suite of helpers.\nThis library provides utilities for interacting with Explicit Settings Models.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Installation](#installation)\n- [Usage](#usage)\n- [Running Tests](#running-tests)\n- [Uploading Package](#uploading-package)\n- [Contributing](#contributing)\n- [License](#license)\n- [Contact](#contact)\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Edgegap Settings library includes various tools and helpers for interacting with Explicit Settings Models. It is\ndesigned for use within the Edgegap organization.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install this library, ensure you have Python and `poetry` installed. Then, use the following command:\n\n```bash\npoetry add edgegap-settings\n```\n\nEnsure you have the necessary permissions to install and use this library, as it is intended for Edgegap employees only.\n\n## Usage\n\nPlease consult Obsidian Documentation for Usage\n\n## Running Tests\n\nTo run tests for this library, you need to have pytest installed. You can install dev dependencies with:\n\n```bash\npoetry install --with=dev\n```\n\nthen run\n\n```bash\npytest\n```\n\nThis will execute all the tests in the tests folder.\n\n## Uploading Package\n\nTo upload the distribution to pypi, you will need an API token from Pypi\n\n```bash\npoetry config pypi-token.pypi <your-api-token>\npoetry version x.x.x\npoetry publish --build\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\nIf you'd like to contribute to this library and you're an Edgegap employee, please follow these steps:\n\n- Fork the repository.\n- Create a new branch for your changes (e.g., feature/my-feature).\n- Commit your changes with a clear message.\n- Push your branch to your fork.\n- Open a Pull Request, explaining the changes and providing any necessary context.\n\n## License\n\nThis software is proprietary to Edgegap. Only current Edgegap employees are allowed to use this library. Refer to the\nLICENSE file for detailed licensing information.\n\n## Contact\n\nFor support or questions related to this library, please contact support@edgegap.com.\n\n## Acknowledgements\n\nThanks to the Edgegap development team for creating and maintaining this library."], "modules": [{"name": "edgegap_settings._factory", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.fmt", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.handler", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.SettingsFactory", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.SettingsFactory.from_settings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "settings", "type": {"name": "type", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "edgegap_settings._factory.SettingsFa